\ = is structural on matrices (shape then contents); </> are element-wise.

\ = : identical matrices are equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix = . cr       \ 1
\ = : differing element -> not equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 5 ] 2 2 matrix = . cr       \ 0
\ = : differing shape -> not equal
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 2 3 matrix = . cr   \ 0

\ </> : element-wise, a 1.0/0.0 matrix
[ 1 5 3 ] 1 3 matrix [ 2 4 3 ] 1 3 matrix < .            \ [1 0 0]
[ 1 5 3 ] 1 3 matrix [ 2 4 3 ] 1 3 matrix > .            \ [0 1 0]
\ scalar broadcast
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 3 < .                             \ matrix [< scalar -> [[1 1][0 0]]
2 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix < .                            \ scalar [< matrix -> [[0 0][1 1]]
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 > .                            \ matrix >] scalar -> [[0 0][1 1]]
\ mismatched shapes -> error
[ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix < .             \ error: shapes differ

\ matrices still order for set membership (via val_cmp, not the < word)
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 5 ] 2 2 matrix 2 set size . cr  \ 2
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 set size . cr  \ 1
